rial; font-size:12pt">consulted on the roles and remit of various ombudsmen schemes</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> in those countries</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. As a result </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">a single </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">offi</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ce of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Public Services </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Ombudsman</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">was created </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Scotland</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> in 2002 and in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Wales</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> in 2005 in order </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to deal</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> with complaints of maladmi</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ni</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">stration about </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">those </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">devolved </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">bodies who deliver public services.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">  </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 27pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-27pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 27pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-27pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2.2</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">This ‘one stop shop model’ for complaints about publi</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">c administration has, in essence, been in existence in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Northern Ireland</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> since 1969 with the creation of the statutory offices of Parliamentary Commissioner for Administration for </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Northern Ireland</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Northern Ireland</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> Commissioner for Complaints. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">While </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">thes</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">e of</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">f</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ices were rebranded </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">in 1996, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">as Assembly Ombudsman for Northern Ireland and Northern Ireland Commissioner for Complaints </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">respectively, they </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">have</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">since their inception</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> ( with one exception), </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> been </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">held by the same </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">o</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">mbudsman with</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> staff inves</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">tigat</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ing </sp